<p id="short">Home lab on Raspberry Pi for learning.</p>

<div style="padding: 10px;">
  <h2 id="about">About</h2>
  <p>A compact and versatile Raspberry Pi home lab designed for network security, file storage, monitoring with Zabbix, DNS-level ad blocking, task automation via cron, web hosting, code repositories, and containerized services using Docker.</p>

  <h2>Included:</h2>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">VPN</strong> – secure remote access using OpenVPN or WireGuard</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">NAS</strong> – network-attached storage for centralized file sharing</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Monitoring</strong> – system and network monitoring with Zabbix</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Adblock DNS</strong> – blocking ads at DNS level for the entire network</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Cron scheduler</strong> – automating tasks and maintenance jobs</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Web server</strong> – hosting simple websites and applications (e.g., Nginx)</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Git server</strong> – local code repositories and configuration management</p>
  <p><strong style="color: aqua;">Docker</strong> – containerization for easy deployment and management of services</p>
</div>








